\frac {B+C}{2}
| \frac {A+D}{2} - \frac {B+C} {2}|
  | \frac {A+B}{2} - \frac {C+D}{2} | + | \frac {A+D}{2} - \frac {B+C} {2}| = |\frac {A-B}{2} |  + | \frac {B-C} {2} | + | \frac {C-D}{2} | + | \frac {D-A} {2} | 
 | \frac {A+B}{2} - \frac {C+D}{2} | \leq | \frac {A-D} {2} | + | \frac {B-C}{2} | \\  | \frac {A+D}{2} - \frac {B+C} {2}| \leq | \frac {A-B}{2} | + | \frac {D-C}{2} | \\
 A-D \parallel B-C, A-B \parallel D-C 
